{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1274,"text":"What is going to be the future of learning?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":6690,"text":"I do have a plan,"},{"time":8970,"text":"but in order for me to tell you what that plan is,"},{"time":12050,"text":"I need to tell you a little story,"},{"time":15020,"text":"which kind of sets the stage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17866,"text":"I tried to look at"},{"time":19653,"text":"where did the kind of learning we do in schools,"},{"time":23060,"text":"where did it come from?"},{"time":25330,"text":"And you can look far back into the past,"},{"time":27762,"text":"but if you look at present-day schooling the way it is,"},{"time":31575,"text":"it's quite easy to figure out where it came from."},{"time":35277,"text":"It came from about 300 years ago,"},{"time":39225,"text":"and it came from the last"},{"time":41442,"text":"and the biggest of the empires on this planet. [\"The British Empire\"]"},{"time":44410,"text":"Imagine trying to run the show,"},{"time":46755,"text":"trying to run the entire planet,"},{"time":49163,"text":"without computers, without telephones,"},{"time":52987,"text":"with data handwritten on pieces of paper,"},{"time":57119,"text":"and traveling by ships."},{"time":60669,"text":"But the Victorians actually did it."},{"time":62823,"text":"What they did was amazing."},{"time":65991,"text":"They created a global computer"},{"time":69303,"text":"made up of people."},{"time":72359,"text":"It's still with us today."},{"time":74152,"text":"It's called the bureaucratic administrative machine."},{"time":80131,"text":"In order to have that machine running,"},{"time":83458,"text":"you need lots and lots of people."},{"time":86659,"text":"They made another machine to produce those people:"},{"time":91018,"text":"the school."},{"time":93914,"text":"The schools would produce the people"},{"time":96691,"text":"who would then become parts of the"},{"time":100540,"text":"bureaucratic administrative machine."},{"time":103925,"text":"They must be identical to each other."},{"time":108315,"text":"They must know three things:"},{"time":110472,"text":"They must have good handwriting, because the data is handwritten;"},{"time":113512,"text":"they must be able to read;"},{"time":115667,"text":"and they must be able to do multiplication,"},{"time":117946,"text":"division, addition and subtraction in their head."},{"time":121609,"text":"They must be so identical that you could pick one up from New Zealand"},{"time":125136,"text":"and ship them to Canada"},{"time":127471,"text":"and he would be instantly functional."},{"time":131552,"text":"The Victorians were great engineers."},{"time":134421,"text":"They engineered a system that was so robust"},{"time":137910,"text":"that it's still with us today,"},{"time":140365,"text":"continuously producing identical people"},{"time":144341,"text":"for a machine that no longer exists."},{"time":149157,"text":"The empire is gone,"},{"time":152085,"text":"so what are we doing with that design"},{"time":154989,"text":"that produces these identical people,"},{"time":157358,"text":"and what are we going to do next"},{"time":160261,"text":"if we ever are going to do anything else with it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":164181,"text":"[\"Schools as we know them are obsolete\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165871,"text":"So that's a pretty strong comment there."},{"time":167763,"text":"I said schools as we know them now, they're obsolete."},{"time":171557,"text":"I'm not saying they're broken."},{"time":173291,"text":"It's quite fashionable to say that the education system's broken."},{"time":176288,"text":"It's not broken. It's wonderfully constructed."},{"time":179939,"text":"It's just that we don't need it anymore. It's outdated."},{"time":186165,"text":"What are the kind of jobs that we have today?"},{"time":188572,"text":"Well, the clerks are the computers."},{"time":190706,"text":"They're there in thousands in every office."},{"time":193237,"text":"And you have people who guide those computers"},{"time":196442,"text":"to do their clerical jobs."},{"time":198919,"text":"Those people don't need to be able to write beautifully by hand."},{"time":202183,"text":"They don't need to be able to multiply numbers in their heads."},{"time":205215,"text":"They do need to be able to read."},{"time":207487,"text":"In fact, they need to be able to read discerningly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211637,"text":"Well, that's today, but we don't even know"},{"time":214744,"text":"what the jobs of the future are going to look like."},{"time":217303,"text":"We know that people will work from wherever they want,"},{"time":219947,"text":"whenever they want, in whatever way they want."},{"time":223145,"text":"How is present-day schooling going to prepare them"},{"time":227333,"text":"for that world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":229876,"text":"Well, I bumped into this whole thing completely by accident."},{"time":234924,"text":"I used to teach people how to write computer programs"},{"time":237556,"text":"in New Delhi, 14 years ago."},{"time":240020,"text":"And right next to where I used to work, there was a slum."},{"time":243777,"text":"And I used to think, how on Earth are those kids"},{"time":246364,"text":"ever going to learn to write computer programs?"},{"time":248884,"text":"Or should they not?"},{"time":251964,"text":"At the same time, we also had lots of parents,"},{"time":254581,"text":"rich people, who had computers,"},{"time":257012,"text":"and who used to tell me, \"You know, my son,"},{"time":260143,"text":"I think he's gifted,"},{"time":262332,"text":"because he does wonderful things with computers."},{"time":265206,"text":"And my daughter -- oh, surely she is extra-intelligent.\""},{"time":269182,"text":"And so on. So I suddenly figured that,"},{"time":271290,"text":"how come all the rich people are having"},{"time":273086,"text":"these extraordinarily gifted children?"},{"time":275227,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":277142,"text":"What did the poor do wrong?"},{"time":279966,"text":"I made a hole in the boundary wall"},{"time":282969,"text":"of the slum next to my office,"},{"time":285001,"text":"and stuck a computer inside it just to see what would happen"},{"time":287745,"text":"if I gave a computer to children who never would have one,"},{"time":290729,"text":"didn't know any English, didn't know what the Internet was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294065,"text":"The children came running in."},{"time":295017,"text":"It was three feet off the ground, and they said, \"What is this?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":297187,"text":"And I said, \"Yeah, it's, I don't know.\""},{"time":300171,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302387,"text":"They said, \"Why have you put it there?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":304943,"text":"I said, \"Just like that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":306158,"text":"And they said, \"Can we touch it?\"I said, \"If you wish to.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":309167,"text":"And I went away."},{"time":311544,"text":"About eight hours later,"},{"time":313288,"text":"we found them browsing and teaching each other how to browse."},{"time":316243,"text":"So I said, \"Well that's impossible, because --"},{"time":318740,"text":"How is it possible? They don't know anything.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":322281,"text":"My colleagues said, \"No, it's a simple solution."},{"time":325145,"text":"One of your students must have been passing by,"},{"time":327968,"text":"showed them how to use the mouse.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":330063,"text":"So I said, \"Yeah, that's possible.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":331586,"text":"So I repeated the experiment. I went 300 miles out of Delhi"},{"time":334645,"text":"into a really remote village"},{"time":336636,"text":"where the chances of a passing software development engineer"},{"time":340428,"text":"was very little. (Laughter)"},{"time":344844,"text":"I repeated the experiment there."},{"time":347507,"text":"There was no place to stay, so I stuck my computer in,"},{"time":349794,"text":"I went away, came back after a couple of months,"},{"time":351994,"text":"found kids playing games on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353689,"text":"When they saw me, they said,"},{"time":354640,"text":"\"We want a faster processor and a better mouse.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":357122,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":361416,"text":"So I said, \"How on Earth do you know all this?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":364825,"text":"And they said something very interesting to me."},{"time":367280,"text":"In an irritated voice, they said,"},{"time":368945,"text":"\"You've given us a machine that works only in English,"},{"time":371498,"text":"so we had to teach ourselves English in order to use it.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":377583,"text":"That's the first time, as a teacher,"},{"time":379560,"text":"that I had heard the word \"teach ourselves\" said so casually."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384651,"text":"Here's a short glimpse from those years."},{"time":388253,"text":"That's the first day at the Hole in the Wall."},{"time":390900,"text":"On your right is an eight-year-old."},{"time":393138,"text":"To his left is his student. She's six."},{"time":398858,"text":"And he's teaching her how to browse."},{"time":402455,"text":"Then onto other parts of the country,"},{"time":405741,"text":"I repeated this over and over again,"},{"time":408024,"text":"getting exactly the same results that we were."},{"time":411469,"text":"[\"Hole in the wall film - 1999\"]"},{"time":415396,"text":"An eight-year-old telling his elder sister what to do."},{"time":424460,"text":"And finally a girl explaining in Marathi what it is,"},{"time":430017,"text":"and said, \"There's a processor inside.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":434266,"text":"So I started publishing."},{"time":436759,"text":"I published everywhere. I wrote down and measured everything,"},{"time":439314,"text":"and I said, in nine months, a group of children"},{"time":441516,"text":"left alone with a computer in any language"},{"time":444214,"text":"will reach the same standard as an office secretary in the West."},{"time":448729,"text":"I'd seen it happen over and over and over again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453489,"text":"But I was curious to know, what else would they do"},{"time":456221,"text":"if they could do this much?"},{"time":458461,"text":"I started experimenting with other subjects,"},{"time":460989,"text":"among them, for example, pronunciation."},{"time":463957,"text":"There's one community of children in southern India"},{"time":466405,"text":"whose English pronunciation is really bad,"},{"time":469173,"text":"and they needed good pronunciation because that would improve their jobs."},{"time":472693,"text":"I gave them a speech-to-text engine in a computer,"},{"time":476771,"text":"and I said, \"Keep talking into it until it types what you say.\""},{"time":480045,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":484677,"text":"They did that, and watch a little bit of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489861,"text":"Computer: Nice to meet you.Child: Nice to meet you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495373,"text":"Sugata Mitra: The reason I ended with the face"},{"time":497644,"text":"of this young lady over there is because I suspect many of you know her."},{"time":501461,"text":"She has now joined a call center in Hyderabad"},{"time":504957,"text":"and may have tortured you about your credit card bills"},{"time":509679,"text":"in a very clear English accent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514452,"text":"So then people said, well, how far will it go?"},{"time":518829,"text":"Where does it stop?"},{"time":520399,"text":"I decided I would destroy my own argument"},{"time":523762,"text":"by creating an absurd proposition."},{"time":526266,"text":"I made a hypothesis, a ridiculous hypothesis."},{"time":530154,"text":"Tamil is a south Indian language, and I said,"},{"time":531958,"text":"can Tamil-speaking children in a south Indian village"},{"time":534603,"text":"learn the biotechnology of DNA replication in English"},{"time":538108,"text":"from a streetside computer?"},{"time":540355,"text":"And I said, I'll measure them. They'll get a zero."},{"time":542540,"text":"I'll spend a couple of months, I'll leave it for a couple of months,"},{"time":545594,"text":"I'll go back, they'll get another zero."},{"time":547898,"text":"I'll go back to the lab and say, we need teachers."},{"time":552254,"text":"I found a village. It was called Kallikuppam in southern India."},{"time":556317,"text":"I put in Hole in the Wall computers there,"},{"time":558994,"text":"downloaded all kinds of stuff from the Internet about DNA replication,"},{"time":562681,"text":"most of which I didn't understand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565986,"text":"The children came rushing, said, \"What's all this?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":568963,"text":"So I said, \"It's very topical, very important. But it's all in English.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":573971,"text":"So they said, \"How can we understand such big English words"},{"time":577325,"text":"and diagrams and chemistry?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":579403,"text":"So by now, I had developed a new pedagogical method,"},{"time":582227,"text":"so I applied that. I said, \"I haven't the foggiest idea.\""},{"time":585111,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":588306,"text":"\"And anyway, I am going away.\""},{"time":591256,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":595624,"text":"So I left them for a couple of months."},{"time":599213,"text":"They'd got a zero. I gave them a test."},{"time":601848,"text":"I came back after two months"},{"time":602772,"text":"and the children trooped in and said, \"We've understood nothing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":606432,"text":"So I said, \"Well, what did I expect?\""},{"time":608507,"text":"So I said, \"Okay, but how long did it take you"},{"time":612592,"text":"before you decided that you can't understand anything?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":615353,"text":"So they said, \"We haven't given up."},{"time":617301,"text":"We look at it every single day.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":619277,"text":"So I said, \"What? You don't understand these screens"},{"time":621742,"text":"and you keep staring at it for two months? What for?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":624446,"text":"So a little girl who you see just now,"},{"time":626959,"text":"she raised her hand, and she says to me in broken Tamil and English,"},{"time":629691,"text":"she said, \"Well, apart from the fact that"},{"time":631888,"text":"improper replication of the DNA molecule causes disease,"},{"time":635039,"text":"we haven't understood anything else.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":637560,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":643272,"text":"So I tested them."},{"time":647392,"text":"I got an educational impossibility, zero to 30 percent"},{"time":650664,"text":"in two months in the tropical heat"},{"time":652968,"text":"with a computer under the tree in a language they didn't know"},{"time":656408,"text":"doing something that's a decade ahead of their time."},{"time":659480,"text":"Absurd. But I had to follow the Victorian norm."},{"time":664857,"text":"Thirty percent is a fail."},{"time":668257,"text":"How do I get them to pass? I have to get them 20 more marks."},{"time":671193,"text":"I couldn't find a teacher. What I did find was a friend that they had,"},{"time":676030,"text":"a 22-year-old girl who was an accountant"},{"time":678416,"text":"and she played with them all the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680864,"text":"So I asked this girl, \"Can you help them?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":682985,"text":"So she says, \"Absolutely not."},{"time":685256,"text":"I didn't have science in school. I have no idea"},{"time":688333,"text":"what they're doing under that tree all day long. I can't help you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":692862,"text":"I said, \"I'll tell you what. Use the method of the grandmother.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":697393,"text":"So she says, \"What's that?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":698723,"text":"I said, \"Stand behind them."},{"time":700110,"text":"Whenever they do anything, you just say,"},{"time":701732,"text":"'Well, wow, I mean, how did you do that?"},{"time":704529,"text":"What's the next page? Gosh, when I was your age, I could have never done that.'"},{"time":707625,"text":"You know what grannies do.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":710547,"text":"So she did that for two more months."},{"time":712721,"text":"The scores jumped to 50 percent."},{"time":715635,"text":"Kallikuppam had caught up"},{"time":717289,"text":"with my control school in New Delhi,"},{"time":719167,"text":"a rich private school with a trained biotechnology teacher."},{"time":723303,"text":"When I saw that graph I knew there is a way to level the playing field."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728140,"text":"Here's Kallikuppam."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730236,"text":"(Children speaking) Neurons ... communication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738431,"text":"I got the camera angle wrong. That one is just amateur stuff,"},{"time":742122,"text":"but what she was saying, as you could make out,"},{"time":744618,"text":"was about neurons, with her hands were like that,"},{"time":747025,"text":"and she was saying neurons communicate."},{"time":750581,"text":"At 12."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753925,"text":"So what are jobs going to be like?"},{"time":757135,"text":"Well, we know what they're like today."},{"time":759426,"text":"What's learning going to be like? We know what it's like today,"},{"time":761764,"text":"children pouring over with their mobile phones on the one hand"},{"time":764817,"text":"and then reluctantly going to school to pick up their books with their other hand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768590,"text":"What will it be tomorrow?"},{"time":772549,"text":"Could it be that we don't need to go to school at all?"},{"time":777449,"text":"Could it be that, at the point in time when you need to know something,"},{"time":780989,"text":"you can find out in two minutes?"},{"time":784309,"text":"Could it be -- a devastating question,"},{"time":788414,"text":"a question that was framed for me by Nicholas Negroponte --"},{"time":791206,"text":"could it be that we are heading towards or maybe in"},{"time":794245,"text":"a future where knowing is obsolete?"},{"time":797605,"text":"But that's terrible. We are homo sapiens."},{"time":800138,"text":"Knowing, that's what distinguishes us from the apes."},{"time":804055,"text":"But look at it this way."},{"time":805832,"text":"It took nature 100 million years"},{"time":808378,"text":"to make the ape stand up"},{"time":810514,"text":"and become Homo sapiens."},{"time":812698,"text":"It took us only 10,000 to make knowing obsolete."},{"time":816394,"text":"What an achievement that is."},{"time":818576,"text":"But we have to integrate that into our own future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822603,"text":"Encouragement seems to be the key."},{"time":825562,"text":"If you look at Kuppam,"},{"time":826772,"text":"if you look at all of the experiments that I did,"},{"time":829586,"text":"it was simply saying, \"Wow,\" saluting learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836721,"text":"There is evidence from neuroscience."},{"time":839115,"text":"The reptilian part of our brain, which sits in the center of our brain,"},{"time":842317,"text":"when it's threatened, it shuts down everything else,"},{"time":846053,"text":"it shuts down the prefrontal cortex, the parts which learn,"},{"time":849731,"text":"it shuts all of that down."},{"time":852475,"text":"Punishment and examinations are seen as threats."},{"time":856623,"text":"We take our children, we make them shut their brains down,"},{"time":860248,"text":"and then we say, \"Perform.\""},{"time":862944,"text":"Why did they create a system like that?"},{"time":866425,"text":"Because it was needed."},{"time":868071,"text":"There was an age in the Age of Empires"},{"time":870656,"text":"when you needed those people who can survive under threat."},{"time":874926,"text":"When you're standing in a trench all alone,"},{"time":877193,"text":"if you could have survived, you're okay, you've passed."},{"time":881224,"text":"If you didn't, you failed."},{"time":884197,"text":"But the Age of Empires is gone."},{"time":886853,"text":"What happens to creativity in our age?"},{"time":890491,"text":"We need to shift that balance back"},{"time":893506,"text":"from threat to pleasure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896915,"text":"I came back to England looking for British grandmothers."},{"time":900867,"text":"I put out notices in papers saying,"},{"time":903884,"text":"if you are a British grandmother, if you have broadband and a web camera,"},{"time":907304,"text":"can you give me one hour of your time per week for free?"},{"time":910531,"text":"I got 200 in the first two weeks."},{"time":912643,"text":"I know more British grandmothers than anyone in the universe. (Laughter)"},{"time":917551,"text":"They're called the Granny Cloud."},{"time":921366,"text":"The Granny Cloud sits on the Internet."},{"time":923096,"text":"If there's a child in trouble, we beam a Gran."},{"time":927470,"text":"She goes on over Skype and she sorts things out."},{"time":931039,"text":"I've seen them do it from a village called Diggles"},{"time":934658,"text":"in northwestern England,"},{"time":936703,"text":"deep inside a village in Tamil Nadu, India,"},{"time":940007,"text":"6,000 miles away."},{"time":942247,"text":"She does it with only one age-old gesture."},{"time":945823,"text":"\"Shhh.\""},{"time":947538,"text":"Okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":950263,"text":"Watch this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951799,"text":"Grandmother: You can't catch me. You say it."},{"time":956055,"text":"You can't catch me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959823,"text":"Children: You can't catch me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":962791,"text":"Grandmother: I'm the Gingerbread Man.Children: I'm the Gingerbread Man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":968373,"text":"Grandmother: Well done! Very good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972963,"text":"SM: So what's happening here?"},{"time":975421,"text":"I think what we need to look at is"},{"time":977265,"text":"we need to look at learning"},{"time":979646,"text":"as the product of educational self-organization."},{"time":984234,"text":"If you allow the educational process to self-organize,"},{"time":987079,"text":"then learning emerges."},{"time":989570,"text":"It's not about making learning happen."},{"time":991963,"text":"It's about letting it happen."},{"time":994179,"text":"The teacher sets the process in motion"},{"time":997452,"text":"and then she stands back in awe"},{"time":1000171,"text":"and watches as learning happens."},{"time":1002539,"text":"I think that's what all this is pointing at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005492,"text":"But how will we know? How will we come to know?"},{"time":1008244,"text":"Well, I intend to build"},{"time":1009919,"text":"these Self-Organized Learning Environments."},{"time":1013220,"text":"They are basically broadband, collaboration"},{"time":1016905,"text":"and encouragement put together."},{"time":1019298,"text":"I've tried this in many, many schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1021004,"text":"It's been tried all over the world, and teachers"},{"time":1023539,"text":"sort of stand back and say, \"It just happens by itself?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1027165,"text":"And I said, \"Yeah, it happens by itself.\"\"How did you know that?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030282,"text":"I said, \"You won't believe the children who told me"},{"time":1033775,"text":"and where they're from.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036703,"text":"Here's a SOLE in action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039447,"text":"(Children talking)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045556,"text":"This one is in England."},{"time":1051845,"text":"He maintains law and order,"},{"time":1055611,"text":"because remember, there's no teacher around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066096,"text":"Girl: The total number of electrons is not equal to the total number of protons -- SM: Australia"},{"time":1069999,"text":"Girl: -- giving it a net positive or negative electrical charge."},{"time":1076734,"text":"The net charge on an ion is equal to the number of protons"},{"time":1080318,"text":"in the ion minus the number of electrons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1083611,"text":"SM: A decade ahead of her time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1086660,"text":"So SOLEs, I think we need a curriculum of big questions."},{"time":1090263,"text":"You already heard about that. You know what that means."},{"time":1092469,"text":"There was a time when Stone Age men and women"},{"time":1095870,"text":"used to sit and look up at the sky and say,"},{"time":1097974,"text":"\"What are those twinkling lights?\""},{"time":1100453,"text":"They built the first curriculum, but we've lost sight of those wondrous questions."},{"time":1105247,"text":"We've brought it down to the tangent of an angle."},{"time":1109377,"text":"But that's not sexy enough."},{"time":1113085,"text":"The way you would put it to a nine-year-old is to say,"},{"time":1116046,"text":"\"If a meteorite was coming to hit the Earth,"},{"time":1119199,"text":"how would you figure out if it was going to or not?\""},{"time":1122597,"text":"And if he says, \"Well, what? how?\""},{"time":1125157,"text":"you say, \"There's a magic word. It's called the tangent of an angle,\""},{"time":1128142,"text":"and leave him alone. He'll figure it out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1131013,"text":"So here are a couple of images from SOLEs."},{"time":1135471,"text":"I've tried incredible, incredible questions --"},{"time":1141060,"text":"\"When did the world begin? How will it end?\" â€”"},{"time":1145348,"text":"to nine-year-olds."},{"time":1147293,"text":"This one is about what happens to the air we breathe."},{"time":1150269,"text":"This is done by children without the help of any teacher."},{"time":1155227,"text":"The teacher only raises the question,"},{"time":1157611,"text":"and then stands back and admires the answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1161275,"text":"So what's my wish?"},{"time":1165011,"text":"My wish is"},{"time":1167227,"text":"that we design the future of learning."},{"time":1171541,"text":"We don't want to be spare parts"},{"time":1173507,"text":"for a great human computer, do we?"},{"time":1175899,"text":"So we need to design a future for learning."},{"time":1179555,"text":"And I've got to -- hang on,"},{"time":1181191,"text":"I've got to get this wording exactly right,"},{"time":1183891,"text":"because, you know, it's very important."},{"time":1186535,"text":"My wish is to help design a future of learning"},{"time":1188851,"text":"by supporting children all over the world"},{"time":1191085,"text":"to tap into their wonder and their ability to work together."},{"time":1194131,"text":"Help me build this school."},{"time":1196363,"text":"It will be called the School in the Cloud."},{"time":1199699,"text":"It will be a school where children go on these intellectual adventures"},{"time":1204772,"text":"driven by the big questions which their mediators put in."},{"time":1208629,"text":"The way I want to do this"},{"time":1210900,"text":"is to build a facility where I can study this."},{"time":1215260,"text":"It's a facility which is practically unmanned."},{"time":1218060,"text":"There's only one granny"},{"time":1219827,"text":"who manages health and safety."},{"time":1222268,"text":"The rest of it's from the cloud."},{"time":1223701,"text":"The lights are turned on and off by the cloud,"},{"time":1225616,"text":"etc., etc., everything's done from the cloud."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1227644,"text":"But I want you for another purpose."},{"time":1230869,"text":"You can do Self-Organized Learning Environments"},{"time":1233628,"text":"at home, in the school, outside of school, in clubs."},{"time":1238644,"text":"It's very easy to do. There's a great document"},{"time":1240772,"text":"produced by TED which tells you how to do it."},{"time":1242660,"text":"If you would please, please do it"},{"time":1246036,"text":"across all five continents"},{"time":1248401,"text":"and send me the data,"},{"time":1250612,"text":"then I'll put it all together, move it into the School of Clouds,"},{"time":1254116,"text":"and create the future of learning."},{"time":1257380,"text":"That's my wish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1259172,"text":"And just one last thing."},{"time":1260595,"text":"I'll take you to the top of the Himalayas."},{"time":1263188,"text":"At 12,000 feet, where the air is thin,"},{"time":1266491,"text":"I once built two Hole in the Wall computers,"},{"time":1269476,"text":"and the children flocked there."},{"time":1270931,"text":"And there was this little girl who was following me around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1273828,"text":"And I said to her, \"You know, I want to give a computer to everybody, every child."},{"time":1278544,"text":"I don't know, what should I do?\""},{"time":1280945,"text":"And I was trying to take a picture of her quietly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1284976,"text":"She suddenly raised her hand like this, and said to me,"},{"time":1289032,"text":"\"Get on with it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1290921,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1302785,"text":"I think it was good advice."},{"time":1304646,"text":"I'll follow her advice. I'll stop talking."},{"time":1306714,"text":"Thank you. Thank you very much."},{"time":1310704,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1314455,"text":"Thank you. Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":1322779,"text":"Thank you very much. Wow. (Applause)"}]}]}